      "url": "http://www.dominionenergy.com/en/Virginia/Rates-and-Tariffs/Understanding-Rates",
      "title": "Understanding Rates | Virginia - Dominion Energy",
      "text": "Understanding Rates | Virginia | Dominion Energy\n\nSearch Close\n\n# Understanding Rates\n\nLearn about your rate and where your payment goes.\n\nVirginia/ Rates and Tariffs\n\n## Electric Rates Overview\n\nYour energy rate helps pay for the cost of delivering electricity to you, and to support projects that will meet the ever-growing demand for more energy. Several factors affect the rate you pay, including how much energy you use, the cost of fuel, the time of year, and your customer type – whether you're a homeowner, business, or industrial user.\n\nThere are two main factors that determine your monthly electric bill:\n\n1. Generating and Delivering Electricity. Electric utility service in Virginia is regulated by the non-partisan State Corporation Commission. Dominion Energy can't raise rates whenever it wants, because it is a regulated utility. The SCC exists to protect customers by ensuring electric rates are fair, reasonable, and tied to the actual cost of providing service – not inflated for ",
      "highlights": [
        " Understanding Rates | Virginia | Dominion Energy\n\nSearch Close\n\n# Understanding Rates  ...    ## Electric Rates Overview Your energy rate helps pay for the cost of delivering electricity to you, and to support projects that will meet the ever-growing demand for more energy. Several factors affect the rate you pay, including how much energy you use, the cost of fuel, the time of year, and your customer type – whether you're a homeowner, business, or industrial user.  ...    1. Generating and Delivering Electricity. Electric utility service in Virginia is regulated by the non-partisan State Corporation Commission. Dominion Energy can't raise rates whenever it wants, because it is a regulated utility. The SCC exists to protect customers by ensuring electric rates are fair, reasonable, and tied to the actual cost of providing service – not inflated for excess profit. Before any rate changes take effect, the SCC thoroughly examines utility proposals, audit expenses, and sets limits on how much profit companies can earn. This oversight helps  ...    Due to routine updates to the grid, the underlying cost of electric service frequently changes, even if your household  ...    ### What Are the Parts of an Electric Bill in Virginia?\n\nWant to better understand each part of your electric bill? Visit Understand My Bill\n\n## Where Does My Dollar Go?\n\n### Your Dollar Broken Down Over 75% of your bill covers power generation and delivery costs, including: - Enabling our system to more easily integrate renewable resources. - Strengthening the power grid against severe weather and physical/cyber security threats. - Burying our most outage-prone overhead neighborhood power lines. - Preparing existing nuclear stations to operate for decades to come.  ...    - A portion of your payment supports capital investments approved by state regulators, helping maintain and improve service. We transfer expenses like fuel and taxes directly, ensuring you're only charged what we 